TextBlock.TextLine: London Henry Maynard
In Antwarp B Aprill 168
th
S. my last to you was on the 29 past, sence recd. yd of 15 ditto in answere of where
please to be referred to the same, for then desired an ofher pack of spanish cloathes
whith I much want in lod prijses: also in ordered 2 blews more & 3 aurovas the which
pray dispatch with all speed & lett the blews be according to the inclosed pattarnes
which in case were not so ready, may come with the spanish cloathes & make up
the auroves to 5 peeces, thought I could rather wish butt 3 & add2 reds of about
£8:10 a £9 ap to send that pack for ward with all speed, whilst bij the by I must
desire that good care betaken in sooking over the auporas & reds, because I finde Irecett
potts & fault in the last wee had in so much, that some have been returned
I should be more urgent for goods, butt slinck that sommer dressing, dying
l ordering is more advantagions in all respects, so that I am butt for the eed
full till further time whilst in the meane while the hem bourg schipping
will be over in the north & goods more plenty to markett. the gold sent
you hath itto full weight, that is to say every peece accordingly to the
lace full weight, not that I know, how much itt doth weiy in all butt I am
confident, they can not be bought better n or cheaper - Ill remitt yo some
mony more for yd acctt. & so by degrees endeavour to procure yd satisfaction
I observe the ship from Hull with our 8 pack is departed, god send itt wel
over, as also the 2 bales from costy, wee have for my weither on our coast
& I have given the necessary orders att Rotterdam our custome offred are
become very swil to Coats, in so much that the goods are repulated
verij well & the charges will be butt little in considerablon of that they
have been, nevertheless, I dare not venter our callicoes as wee did the last
pareell, whoever I have wrott mr. scawen the needfull, mee thinckes that
6 or 7 bales eack of cottons & 2 bajes would bring over the callicoes all
& they could be shipped all att a time in sundrye vessels to againe the kings
mony whoever lett is honnour not be to much oppoled, my thanckes for yd
care & kindness to assort our where house off all truely I have att present
& hadd all this lent good demand & could wish as many goods on hand as
I have butt our poore countrey is meneayed againe with a french blow & un less
yd nation doth aggree & udast us I doubt wee shall not be able to do itt our
selfs which keeps, our corridge some what tyed in for this season, inclosed is
the bill accepted & so rest
Antwarp 1 Aprill
on Abram Vvviins
th
S. my last to you was on the 29: past, sence non from you I desired you to lend
orders in the north to provide 100 bayes from 36: to 45 st a p assorted, besides
some draps & gray cullours cloathes I have obseried that the hom bourg
shipping is not yett over, where for I do iudge that our best time for buying
wall be att the latter end of this month & beginning of may, so that you may
in cordidge yd freind of a great comission butt lett him proceed butt with
little, for wee have all the appoaching summerf or us, as wee did last year
& when goods are well brought, they sell well, there is one mr. Samuell
tijkes att leeds, which is a very good understanding man, butt he is, engaged
for some of the ham brough comp. whoever could you gett him on yd side
itt would be verij advantagions to our ander takeings butt what ever you
speake of him, lett not I be mentioned by ne meanes, so could you gete
hem to undertake yd comissions imploy noother for I have seen his goods
yett forabetter satisfaction in could imploy boath him & ir
other freind, the cloathes must be assorted incullours as to the inclosed
pattarnes & those that cost more then 3:6 ayd must be whole peeces or
broad or lony cloathes & every peece have itts full in casure in all respect
besides the goods must be curiously drest, prest & toilletted & all the packes
to be vrapped with bayes I would same have you to be mighty currous
& exart in driving our intrest from the norch & advise mee fromtme
to time how thenys for I hope & do wish that wee not be disapointed as
least: yeare where fore I beginne in good time & want first of all
